{
  "texts": [
    "We use a global batch size of 32 (on device: 8 with gradient accumulation: 4), and a learning rate of 1e -4.",
    "In End-to-End pretraining procedure, LoRA layers of the model were trained end-to-end for 5 epochs.",
    "In case of Two-Stage pretraining procedure, the embedding layers training phase and keeping LoRA layers frozen, was carried out for 2 epochs on 10K PAC samples.",
    "Then both the LoRA and embedding layers were trained end-to-end on 20K PAC samples for 3 epochs.",
    "In both the pretraining procedures, the base layers of the models were kept frozen throughout the training process."
  ]
}